<subSubSection id="B580F865A93B7D9A437AB5CAA53E0E39" pageId="0" pageNumber="111" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="3D0CAE3C5BF2A25580F9465693A2938D" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">
<taxonomicName id="4113095F697C754D3BA482F10C17CFD4" LSID="EC78791B-5218-518A-BF6A-8790499C04BA" authority="Horik., J. Sci. Hiroshima Univ., Ser. B, Div. 2, Bot. 2: 186. 1934." class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Calypogeiaceae" genus="Calypogeia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Calypogeia formosana" order="Jungermanniales" pageId="0" pageNumber="111" phylum="Marchantiophyta" rank="species" species="formosana">Calypogeia formosana Horik., J. Sci. Hiroshima Univ., Ser. B, Div. 2, Bot. 2: 186. 1934.</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8CD188412C5504B663956A1D386F86B2" pageId="0" pageNumber="111" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="2827C1009CD6226C7B236656CACA70AA" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8459E755732C8081A7D695BCA9EAF9A5" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">Taiwan (Formosa). Mt. Morrison, August 1932, Y. Horikawa, no. 9124; not seen.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="2F59265DC1E85B807C7019BD91DA5FDA" pageId="0" pageNumber="111" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="7BA6206A780B0590A2003B9B0FBCA57D" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="61C4CCC8CF133CA08446B9552483C9B7" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">
This is a Taiwan endemic species (
<bibRefCitation id="62E16B7B9EB7EDBC62F0D44BEE3B9481" author="Horikawa, Y" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin, University Museum, University of Tokyo" pageId="0" pageNumber="111" refId="B33" refString="Horikawa, Y, 1934. Monographia hepaticarum australi-japonicarum. Journal of Science of the Hiroshima University: Series B, Division 2 (Botany) 2: 101-325." title="Monographia hepaticarum australi-japonicarum. Journal of Science of the Hiroshima University: Series B, Division 2 (Botany) 2: 101 - 325." year="1934">Horikawa 1934</bibRefCitation>
) that may be expected in the eastern Meta-Himalaya. The taxon has unclear relationships (placed into &quot;incertae sedis&quot; in 
<bibRefCitation id="1694BDC7650B20DACFD3240F01AEBD78" DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/phytokeys.59.6261" author="Soederstroem, L" journalOrPublisher="PhytoKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="111" pagination="1 - 828" refId="B65" refString="Soederstroem, L, Hagborg, A, von Konrat, M, Bartholomew-Began, S, Bell, D, Briscoe, L, Brown, E, Cargill, DC, Costa, DP, Crandall-Stotler, BJ, Cooper, ED, Dauphin, G, Engel, JJ, Feldberg, K, Glenny, D, Gradstein, SR, He, X, Heinrichs, J, Hentschel, J, Ilkiu-Borges, AL, Katagiri, T, Konstantinova, NA, Larrain, J, Long, DG, Nebel, M, Pocs, T, Felisa Puche, F, Reiner-Drehwald, E, Renner, MAM, Sass-Gyarmati, A, Schaefer-Verwimp, A, Moragues, JGS, Stotler, RE, Sukkharak, P, Thiers, BM, Uribe, J, Vana, J, Villarreal, JC, Wigginton, M, Zhang, L, Zhu, R-L, 2016. World checklist of hornworts and liverworts. PhytoKeys 59: 1 - 828, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/phytokeys.59.6261" title="World checklist of hornworts and liverworts." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/phytokeys.59.6261" volume="59" year="2016">
<normalizedToken id="13D637D0E21C62EB85813FFDAFF978F7" originalValue="Söderström">Soederstroem</normalizedToken>
et al. 2016
</bibRefCitation>
), and by morphology (as it could be estimated from the description and illustration) it is related to 
<taxonomicName id="AD2CE74BF69AB691A434F8A71DE3F57D" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Calypogeiaceae" genus="Calypogeia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Calypogeia integristipula" order="Jungermanniales" pageId="0" pageNumber="111" phylum="Marchantiophyta" rank="species" species="integristipula">
<emphasis id="8C0CF39E1A230BD6C4914526AAC36CE2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">Calypogeia integristipula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, from which, however, it differs in acute leaves. Acute leaves are also similar to many other 
<taxonomicName id="14590B4710DED8F30A017A632E5AB3EF" authorityName="Raddi" authorityYear="1818" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Calypogeiaceae" genus="Calypogeia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Calypogeia" order="Jungermanniales" pageId="0" pageNumber="111" phylum="Marchantiophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3BC1D471A8267D7ECEE571CA8ACF741E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">Calypogeia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
that are recorded or may be expected in the Sino-Himalaya, but all of them have more deeply (more than 1/2) divided underleaves, versus only short and lunate sinus in 
<taxonomicName id="36786880D0CB1A5F8E45F0021CF9BA5B" genus="C." lsidName="C. formosana" pageId="0" pageNumber="111" rank="species" species="formosana">
<emphasis id="33D3DB2484F490080AE02EF874DBFB5E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">C. formosana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
underleaves. Another possible morphological relative of 
<taxonomicName id="626147C9914F5C1FAC48ACB0B299DB38" genus="C." lsidName="C. formosana" pageId="0" pageNumber="111" rank="species" species="formosana">
<emphasis id="3F02F28345E03C5EEBE72335F5E93E29" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">C. formosana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is 
<taxonomicName id="D6CB0AAE3FEED50C6FBB96C31FAFBDFC" genus="C." lsidName="C. neesiana" pageId="0" pageNumber="111" rank="species" species="neesiana">C. neesiana</taxonomicName>
ssp. 
<taxonomicName id="3A8BB276554951533715036E9094FE0C" genus="C." lsidName="subsp. subalpina" pageId="0" pageNumber="111" rank="subSpecies" species="neesiana" subSpecies="subalpina">subalpina</taxonomicName>
, which is characterized by orbicular and shortly divided underleaves. The two taxa, however, differ in their leaf apex features.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B50033028E6AC052B6DDD1CDDC8E3FD1" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">
<emphasis id="DA59A3B29FC0DCBF48C6D7922167691C" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">
<taxonomicName id="3C3E5D636E9548B33CC277506CF64382" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Calypogeiaceae" genus="Calypogeia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Calypogeia goebelii" order="Jungermanniales" pageId="0" pageNumber="111" phylum="Marchantiophyta" rank="species" species="goebelii">Calypogeia goebelii</taxonomicName>
var. 
<taxonomicName id="22A789901AEDA5EFAFAB7E314A1E80E9" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Calypogeiaceae" genus="Calypogeia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="var. siamensis" order="Jungermanniales" pageId="0" pageNumber="111" phylum="Marchantiophyta" rank="variety" species="goebelii" variety="siamensis">siamensis</taxonomicName>
N.Kitag., Beih. Nova Hedwigia 90: 165. 1988.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C8C586F9269557682583DEA2D234C291" pageId="0" pageNumber="111" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="290EF80944D9BB14FC762452E865377D" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="298DAC3E7A0797B0728D4D6BD8331E32" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">Thailand. Nakawn Sritamarat: Mt. Khao Luang, M. Tagawa &amp; N. Kitagawa (holotype: KYO [T4737]); not seen.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FCBD11882C61DE5CEF0A83596B6AD117" pageId="0" pageNumber="111" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="64719D232529ECDECED13180BEAF0875" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E02F034781C4FCFFA85D18E7B57FE37E" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">
The taxon is known only from the type that is from southern Thailand (
<bibRefCitation id="91BDFC6405FF963533F4C7FF71766F50" author="Kitagawa, N" journalOrPublisher="Nova Hedwigia" pageId="0" pageNumber="111" pagination="163 - 170" refId="B39" refString="Kitagawa, N, 1988. Studies on the Hepaticae of Thailand V. The family Calypogeiaceae. Nova Hedwigia 90: 163 - 170" title="Studies on the Hepaticae of Thailand V. The family Calypogeiaceae." volume="90" year="1988">Kitagawa 1988</bibRefCitation>
) and was never recorded for the Sino-Himalaya. This taxon is indeed different from true 
<taxonomicName id="DB50AA27466AA55A8BADA500B2ECAD60" genus="C." lsidName="C. goebelii" pageId="0" pageNumber="111" rank="species" species="goebelii">
<emphasis id="DC96EA6F56F4E6DF26FF18D2FBA879D2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">C. goebelii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
due to considerably larger leaf cells, more deeply bilobed leaves and fragile apical leaf teeth. This taxon may belong to a species not yet described, but to draw any conclusions, new collections that are suitable for molecular analysis and/or for study of oil body characteristics are needed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
